Oshodi market in Lagos was on Monday thrown in disarray as thugs reportedly prevented traders from opening their stores to begin commercial activities for the day. Video footage posted on Twitter showed armed security operatives trying to restore calm in the market Spokesman to Lagos State Police Command Chike Otti said he was not aware of the issue. Our correspondent gathered shops in the market were yet to be opened at about 9:15 a.m. Details later. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .